

Transcribe any audio or YouTube video with OpenAI Whisper and get AI-powered summaries, topics, and named entities via Mistral — all from a clean browser interface.

---

## Demo

> Upload an audio file or paste a YouTube URL → Whisper transcribes → Mistral summarizes → results in seconds.

---

## How It Works

```
Audio File / YouTube URL
        ↓
  audio_utils.py     → Download + preprocess audio (mono, 16kHz, normalized)
        ↓
  transcriber.py     → Transcribe audio to text (OpenAI Whisper)
        ↓
  summarizer.py      → Summarize transcript (Mistral AI via LangChain)
        ↓
  pipeline.py        → Orchestrates all stages
        ↓
  app.py             → Gradio browser interface
```

---

## Features

- Paste any YouTube URL and transcribe it instantly
- Upload your own audio file (MP3, WAV, M4A, OGG, and more)
- Automatic language detection across 99+ languages
- Structured summaries — overview, key points, conclusion
- Key topic extraction and named entity recognition
- Output summary in English, Hindi, Spanish, French, or German
- Choose Whisper model size based on speed vs accuracy tradeoff
- Clean browser UI — no terminal needed

---

## Project Structure

```
audie/
├── app.py              # Gradio browser interface
├── pipeline.py         # Main orchestrator
├── audio_utils.py      # Audio download and preprocessing
├── transcriber.py      # Whisper transcription
├── summarizer.py       # LangChain + Mistral summarization
├── .env                # API keys (never commit this)
├── requirements.txt    # Dependencies
└── uploads/            # Auto-created, stores processed audio files
```

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.9+
- FFmpeg installed on your system
- Mistral API key

### Install FFmpeg

**Ubuntu/Debian:**
```bash
sudo apt install ffmpeg
```

**macOS:**
```bash
brew install ffmpeg
```

**Windows:**
Download from [ffmpeg.org](https://ffmpeg.org/download.html) and add to PATH.

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/rohn-negi/whisper-mistral-summarizer.git
cd audie
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Create a `.env` file in the project root:
```
MISTRAL_API_KEY=your_mistral_api_key_here
```

---

## Usage

### Browser UI
```bash
python app.py
```
Opens at `http://127.0.0.1:7860` in your browser.

### Terminal
```bash
python pipeline.py
```
Prompts you for URL/file, model, and language directly in the terminal.

---

## Whisper Model Guide

| Model  | Size   | Speed         | Best For                  |
|--------|--------|---------------|---------------------------|
| tiny   | 39M    | ~32x realtime | Quick tests               |
| base   | 74M    | ~16x realtime | Fast, decent accuracy     |
| small  | 244M   | ~6x realtime  | Good balance              |
| medium | 769M   | ~2x realtime  | Recommended default       |
| large  | 1550M  | ~1x realtime  | Best accuracy, needs GPU  |

---

## Output

| Field       | Description                                              |
|-------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| Transcript  | Full verbatim text of everything spoken                  |
| Summary     | Structured markdown — overview, key points, conclusion   |
| Key Topics  | Up to 5 main themes discussed                            |
| Entities    | People, places, organizations, and products mentioned    |

---

## Dependencies

```
openai-whisper
yt-dlp
pydub
gradio
langchain
langchain-mistralai
langchain-core
python-dotenv
```

---

## Notes

- Whisper models are downloaded automatically on first use and cached locally
- All audio is saved to `uploads/` after processing
- For long audio on CPU, expect the `large` model to be slow — a GPU is recommended
- The `uploads/` folder is created automatically on first run

